riod help to contextualise a specifically fin de siècle model of death.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGothic fiction (Literary genre), EnglishxHistory and criticism. 4aGothic 2017. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aCorpse.  aCreativity.  aDeath.  aGothic.  aRomanticism.  aUncanny.  aWriting.  anineteenth century.1 aSmith, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610107540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526101075423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526101075/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles